		<div id="comment_body_64340095"><p>
Typically, heavy transport drivers (and other types, varying from state-to-state) have an "hours of service" app on a phone or tablet, where they set whether they are on/off duty. This app needs to know whether or not the vehicle has been driving, for how long, and for how far. So it talks with the ELD via bluetooth to request this information. The app needs this information because it is required by the federal government (DOT), as well as things required, or superceded by state law. DOT inspectors exist,<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
